[[deprecated]] is a standard attribute introduced in C++14 to mark functions, classes, variables, enums, etc., as deprecated.

It tells the compiler to generate a warning whenever the deprecated entity is used

[[deprecated]] is a C++14 standard attribute used to mark APIs as obsolete. 
The compiler issues a warning when the deprecated function, class, variable, or enum is used, optionally displaying a custom message.

#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

[[deprecated("Use newFunction() instead")]]
void oldFunction() {
    cout << "Old\n";
}

void newFunction() {
    cout << "New\n";
}

int main() {
    oldFunction();   // Warning
    newFunction();
}
